skirting
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:[woolhandling] the trimming of soiled or untidy wool from the edge of a fleece before rolling and pressing.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: the process; see also skirting, the product
